## 6. Advance Techniques (Beyond Headers)

### 6.1 Verb Tampering
Different HTTP methods same endpoint pe alag access control follow karte hain — GET block ho toh HEAD, POST, PUT, DELETE, TRACE try karo. Kai backend frameworks sirf GET/POST filter karte hain, baaki methods bhool jaate hain.

### 6.2 Parameter Pollution for Admin Bypass
| Technique | Example |
|---|---|
| Duplicate param | `?admin=false&admin=true` |
| Array injection | `?admin[]=true` |
| JSON type juggling | `{"admin": "true"}` vs `{"admin": true}` vs `{"admin": 1}` |

### 6.3 Race Condition on Access Control
Agar role-check aur action ke beech time gap hai, Burp Turbo Intruder se parallel requests bhejo — kabhi kabhi check bypass ho jaata hai kyunki backend state update hone se pehle hi second request process ho jaati hai.

### 6.4 JWT/Token Manipulation for Admin Access
| Technique | Detail |
|---|---|
| `alg: none` attack | Signature verification bypass — algorithm ko "none" set karke fake token banao |
| Role claim tampering | JWT payload mein `role: user` ko `role: admin` change karo (agar signature verify nahi ho raha) |
| Key confusion (RS256 → HS256) | Public key ko HMAC secret ki tarah use karke fake signed token banao |

### 6.5 Internal API/GraphQL Introspection
Admin panels ke peeche kabhi internal API hoti hai — `/graphql` pe introspection query bhejo, hidden admin mutations/queries expose ho sakte hain.

### 6.6 Cache-Based Bypass
`X-Forwarded-Host` ya cache key manipulation se cached admin response ko poison karke doosre users tak leak karwa sakte ho (web cache poisoning + access control combo).

### 6.7 Host Header Injection
| Header | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `Host: internal-admin.target.com` | Virtual host routing confuse karke internal panel expose karna |
| `X-Forwarded-Server: internal.target.com` | Same purpose, alt header |

